<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,834,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Head as 
<figureCitation box="[518,600,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
. The frons with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with one that is more robust. Postpedicels without SPS vesicles, and as 
<figureCitation box="[1013,1096,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
. Proboscis from below as 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
. Thorax yellow. Three notopleural bristles, with no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron as 
<figureCitation box="[1231,1312,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
. Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdomen as 
<figureCitation box="[1056,1139,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Figs 38– 39</figureCitation>
. Legs yellow apart from brown tip to hind femur. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 longer than 4 (
<figureCitation box="[387,472,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.73 times its length (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1359,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[258,341,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with 10 robust differentiated posterodorsal hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1120,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) and without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[654,736,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–44" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[348,1248,198,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[317,1270,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–44. Megaselia carlkahleri sp. n. male. 32. head;. 33 postpedicel. 34. ventral face of proboscis. 35. notopleuron and mesopleurn. 36. left face of abdomen. 37–39. hypopygium. 40. front tarsus. 41. mid tibia. 42. hind femur. 43. hind tibia. 44. wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617701/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[750,850,1086,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.76" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="1.76">1.76 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.52. Costal ratios 2.31: 1.64: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[456,559,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long. Hair at base of vein 3 
<quantity box="[901,1004,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
long. With 2 axillary bristles. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,762,1435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,1194,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck, W." box="[504,697,1194,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" refId="ref7421" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica. Part UI. Pipunculidae, Phoridae. Wesley, London, 455 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
to Group VI couplet 14 lead 
<specimenCount box="[1024,1076,1195,1219]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wood)" authorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[1045,1076,1196,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="propinqua">
<emphasis box="[1045,1076,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
propinqua (Wood), from which it differs in having spinose labella. In the key to the males of the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[1025,1177,1230,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref7235" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 203, where neither option fits, or to couplet 228 lead 
<specimenCount box="[690,741,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen)" authorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" box="[710,741,1268,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[710,741,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
lata (Meigen) which it closely resembles except the latter is a very dark species. If one follows the note to this couplet one proceeds to couplet 238, lead 
<specimenCount box="[1165,1217,1303,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zetterstedt)" authorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1187,1217,1303,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1187,1217,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
minor (Zetterstedt) which is likewise very similar except for its brown thorax, abdominal tergites, legs and haltere. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1212,1349,1338,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Carl Kähler, who with his sister Gerda, founded 15-juni-fonden, a foundation that has helped Esben Bøggild purchase microscope equipment to facilitate his studies.
</paragraph>
